-- Cia. Albertina Shuts Down Brazil Sugar-Cane Plant, Estado says
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2012-02-06T18:12:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/cia-albertina-shuts-down-brazil-sugar-cane-plant-estado-says.html
Cia. Albertina, a Brazilian sugar-
cane processor that’s been in bankruptcy protection since 2008,
shut its mill in the southeastern city of Sertaozinho, O Estado
de Sao Paulo reported.  Albertina fired 600 of the plant’s workforce, the Sao
Paulo-based newspaper said today on its website, citing Marcelo
Milliet, a manager.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at 
 landberg@bloomberg.net  